Collections pour tags :

Description :

1

Another super pack, this time with 16 different boltgun scaled red dots/scopes, 6 light/laser modules and one motion tracker. I went a bit crazy with the details and can't guarantee that all of them will be visible considering the size of the models, though most should be visible with any basic resin printer. Optics are divided between two STL files while weapon modules are grouped in one STL file. As always, let me know if you have any questions or complaints. Enjoy.

Collections pour tags :

  • 28mm IMP Bits NONDL NONSUP

Description :

1
2
3

An updated version of my previous (now deactivated) file pack for a robotic arm which I made months back. Besides fixing some geometry and STL file issues which were present in the first pack, I also decided to add some additional details to it. The components of the arms are left separate to hopefully avoid non manifold geometry issues as well as allowing anyone to separate the arms for reposing. The claw is also separate from the arm now, allowing some extra freedom in posing. The base and arm also have a slot for a 6mmx3mm circular magnet to keep the two parts together without needing to permanently attach them.

Hope you all enjoy this one and feel free to reach out to me if you encounter any issues with the models. Enjoy

A blockier rendition of the Space Marine power pack. The mounting point for attaching the pack is based on the round nub on firstborn marine models. I'm unsure if it will work with primaris models, but I can make whatever necessary changes needed to make them fit. Feel free to message me if you need anything tweaked.

item.title: [GRATUIT] Cults3d > KeeganLex > Vulcan_Mega_Bolter [non dl]
item.description:
Source : https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/vulcan-mega-bolter-keeganlex

Id objet : vulcan-mega-bolter-keeganlex

Prix : 0 euros

Collections :

  • epic titans IMP Admech-titans-warhounds

Collections pour tags :

  • epic titans IMP Admech-titans-warhounds NONDL NONSUP

Description :

1
2
3

I personally love Warhound Titans and have a full size one printed and painted, though I was never a fan of how the Vulcan Mega Bolters look like a brick with a magazine which would run empty after 5 seconds of continuous fire. This is my attempt to make something more visually striking and with a magazine more suitable for such an immense weapon. The arm mount is sized to other arm mounts which can be found on Cults for free. Just to mix things up a bit, I created a version of the Mega Bolter with twin short barrels and long barrels. The full pack comes with two complete Bolters with short/long barrel along with separate parts for those who want to print separate objects. As always, hope you all enjoy and don't hesitate to contact me with any concerns you may have.

The photographed Bolter is a test print using Nylon 12.

One of several attempts I made to create a miniature minigun to attach to some Ambot models I have. The base profile is too large to work for the Necromunda Ambot models, but it will work just fine for any model with a flat surface. the cannon is scaled for standard bolter rounds though can be increased in size for whatever you need. As always, let me know if there's any issues with the file. I plan on creating some paid model packs soon but want to make sure the meshes of my files are solid before I try charging money for anything.
